last_episode_to_air.name: Sinking Boats, Stealing Deer
last_episode_to_air.overview: Game Warden Allison Hatten discovers a boat with children aboard sinking fast in rough waters. A landowner accuses his neighbour of shooting a trophy buck illegally, and game wardens track down a pair of lawbreaking anglers.

name: Lone Star Law
overview: Follow Viewers get unprecedented access to the more than 500 agents of Texas Parks and Wildlife wardens who embark on dangerous missions to apprehend those who commit crimes against nature. The series captures the more than 60,000 arrests each year made by the wardens as they execute undercover stings, work on ongoing investigations and protect their territories.

episodes.name: Game On
episodes.overview: Texas Game Wardens protect the natural resources of this vast state while fighting crime. An alligator poacher brags online and Wardens go after him. Down on the border Wardens pull illegal nets from the river while looking for drug smugglers. A giant turtle is rescued during a deer poaching investigation.

episodes.name: Caught Red Handed
episodes.overview: Texas Game Wardens go undercover to stop a black market for buying and selling wild animals. A trio of Wardens work the beaches of Galveston and mobilize when an oil spill threatens wildlife. A robotic deer decoy is used to catch night hunters. Teens on jet skis cause problems for the Wardens.

episodes.name: Gulf Recon
episodes.overview: A specialty team of Texas Game Wardens spends a week on a floating cabin to stop drug smuggling operations across the border. The K-9 unit is called in to investigate a woman who may be killing owls to sell exotic headdresses.

episodes.name: Calm Before the Storm
episodes.overview: Across Texas, boating and fishing patrols are interrupted by record storms and flooding. Near Austin, Search and Rescue teams save multiple people from dangerous swift water and tornadoes. Wardens chase a felon with an illegal gun in East Texas.

episodes.name: Mayday Mayday
episodes.overview: The wardens investigate a Jet Ski accident that sends a man to the hospital. Then the wardens must track down a hunter shooting doves in a residential neighborhood. On Lake Lewisville, wardens deal with a partier who's had too much to drink.

episodes.name: Gator Bait
episodes.overview: Wardens search for an alligator that bit a man and his 13-year old son. In West Texas, an abandoned car leads the Wardens to believe a teenage girl may be missing. A man is suspected of hunting on his neighbor's property without permission.

episodes.name: To Catch a Poacher
episodes.overview: A team of Wardens deploy on a multi-county night operation to stop spotlighters and road hunters. Texas Game Wardens check teal hunters on opening weekend. A dead deer found with an arrow still in it leads Game Wardens to a poacher.

episodes.name: Gator vs Dog
episodes.overview: Dove season starts off with a bang, keeping Game Wardens across the state busy from sunrise to sun down. Texas Game Wardens must relocate a 230 kg gator that's loose in a suburban area. Wardens uncover a large marijuana grow hidden in a wildlife preserve.

episodes.name: Caught on Camera
episodes.overview: Game Wardens look for the elusive bighorn sheep in the mountains of West Texas.

episodes.name: Gator vs. Game Warden
episodes.overview: Texas Game Wardens patrol the inland waterways and the Gulf of Mexico. A nuisance alligator gets too close for comfort. Illegal fish lead to multiple citations. A suburban squirrel hunter gets caught trespassing. Wardens race to free an injured deer.

episodes.name: New Blood
episodes.overview: Two new rookies from the 59th cadet class of Texas Game Wardens work their first cases. Game wardens rescue soft-shell turtles caught on illegal trot lines on Llano River. In East Texas, the search is on for a hunter lost in the Big Thicket Preserve.

episodes.name: The Eagle Has Landed
episodes.overview: Texas Game Wardens are busy enforcing fish and game law. An injured bald eagle needs medical attention. Game Wardens go undercover to catch someone selling illegal alligator parts. A tip leads to an angler with multiple undersized fish.

episodes.name: Run and You're Done
episodes.overview: It's dove season in Texas, the start of hunting season. In Beaumont, road hunters get an early start on deer season during a decoy sting. Near Texarkana, a rogue gator is lassoed. On the Gulf Coast, undersized angling means citations.

episodes.name: Moving Target
episodes.overview: Game Wardens beef up patrols for the short pronghorn season. A deer needs to be captured and relocated from an industrial site, and an injured hawk is rushed to a rehabber. Near Port Aransas, Game Wardens check duck hunters on the bay.

episodes.name: Border Bust
episodes.overview: Down on the Mexican border, Game Wardens pull in an illegal gill net. A group caught trespassing is found with firearms and narcotics. In East Texas, Game Wardens question a man suspected of illegally hunting on private property.

episodes.name: Roadside Sting
episodes.overview: It’s opening weekend of deer season and Game Wardens head out around the state to ensure everyone plays by the rules. In East Texas, an injured owl is rushed to the vet. On the Gulf, Game Wardens get tough when an oysterman’s catch doesn’t add up.

episodes.name: Gator Showdown
episodes.overview: Texas Game Wardens are deep into deer season, investigating a suspected poacher and a felon who shouldn't be using a firearm to hunt. An alligator and her hatchlings must be captured and relocated from an East Texas school.

episodes.name: Wild Encounters
episodes.overview: Wardens wrangle a loose bull and relocate a herd of pronghorn.

episodes.name: Armed and Dangerous
episodes.overview: Wardens find an unlicensed hunter who killed a deer after hunting hours.

episodes.name: Don't Mess With Texas
episodes.overview: Game Wardens search for an endangered Whooping Crane. A local beauty shop owner finds an injured baby hawk. Wardens respond to a call about a nuisance alligator and suspicions of a deer poacher arise.

episodes.name: In The Nick of Time
episodes.overview: In Texas, a new year brings new cadets, and a rookie almost gets run down. In Beaumont, Game Warden Boone investigates an armed trespasser. Game Wardens encounter a Mexican boat on U.S. waters while looking for illegal gill nets on the Rio Grande.

episodes.name: Thousand Year Flood
episodes.overview: Texas Summer has Game Wardens Chelsea and Ben rushing to a call about a capsized canoe. Game Warden Deschaaf investigates a trapped deer that leads to more questions than answers. At Canyon Lake, Game Wardens assist in the arrest of a man with a warrant.

episodes.name: Trespassers Beware
episodes.overview: Hurricane Harvey makes landfall. Game Warden Sims sifts through the wreckage on the coast. In Houston, the Game Wardens work on evacuating families from the floods. While Wardens in East Texas rescue people and animals from the Neches River spilling over.

episodes.name: The Face of Danger
episodes.overview: The Game Warden's marine team searches a foreign cargo vessel in the Gulf of Mexico. A man is suspected of pouching 15 deer out of season and the Game Wardens discover a large marijuana growing operation outside of Dallas.

episodes.name: Danger at Dawn
episodes.overview: Texas Game Wardens are all hands on deck after a massive flash flood. Game Wardens rush to a gas station that could explode. A patrol through the Rio Grande leads to an unexpected encounter. Game Wardens investigate an illegally killed hawk.

episodes.name: Submerged
episodes.overview: Texas Game Wardens are all hands on deck after a massive flash flood. Game Wardens rush to a gas station that could explode. A patrol through the Rio Grande leads to an unexpected encounter. Game Wardens investigate an illegally killed hawk.

episodes.name: Chase On The Border
episodes.overview: When the Texas Game Wardens encounter a sick bald eagle, it becomes a race against time to ensure its survival. While checking deer camps near the border of Mexico, a Warden finds himself in a high stakes foot pursuit.

episodes.name: When Deer Attack
episodes.overview: Game Wardens patrol the Rio Grande in search of an unidentified body. Warden Powell investigates an unusual deer case. Wardens Boone and Ataya respond to a call about mountain lions being shot in a woman's backyard.

episodes.name: Poachers & Liars
episodes.overview: Warden Tommy Johnson pays a surprise visit to the home of a known poacher. Warden Mike Boone relocates an alligator snapping turtle. Wardens Inman and Eddins get a poacher to confess. Warden Jennifer Provaznik educates fishermen on the Texas coastline.

episodes.name: Shock on the Bay
episodes.overview: On the Gulf, hundreds of sea turtles face death during a cold spell. A tip leads to a raid on a deer poacher in central Texas. Wardens crack down on white-tailed deer hunters throughout the state.

episodes.name: Poaching Rampage
episodes.overview: Game Wardens investigate an illegal deer hunting case that becomes the largest deer poaching case in Texas history. Youth hunters are taught how to hunt and harvest animals. Warden Inman confronts a man suspected of shooting deer off a public road.

episodes.name: Justice Served
episodes.overview: On Lake Sam Rayburn, a water patrol turns into a cry for help; the wardens serve a warrant to a man who illegally shot a hog; a drug arrest leads a game warden into a manhunt.

episodes.name: Back Road Bait
episodes.overview: It's snapper season on the Gulf and the game wardens catching fishermen who are breaking the law; two men are investigated for cruelty to a wild pig; a jet ski collision leads to arguments; an exotic tortoise finds a new home.

episodes.name: Seeing Stars and Stripes
episodes.overview: It's summertime in Texas and the game wardens handle a speeding jet ski, drunk boaters, angry campers and a rowdy raccoon.

episodes.name: Crash Course
episodes.overview: A feisty gator in Galveston County needs a new home; shrimpers try to conceal their catch; a family's property is damaged by stray bullets; the wardens stage a boat crash.

episodes.name: Wet And Wild
episodes.overview: A festival attracts thousands of people to float the San Marcos River; a patrol on Lake Texoma leads to multiple arrests; a fisherman can't provide identification.

episodes.name: Deceived
episodes.overview: A running deer must be caught before it hurts itself; the game wardens investigate an impersonation case in which a man claims to be one of their own; Richards comes across a suspicious group while he is patrolling Lake Tawakoni.

episodes.name: High Desert Drama
episodes.overview: The Game Wardens investigate reports of wolves as pets and release turtles.

episodes.name: Fawn Stars
episodes.overview: In Liberty County, the death of a deer is investigated; fawns in Harris County are being illegally kept as pets; patrol on Somerville Lake leads to multiple citations; a suspicious car is stopped in Red River County.

episodes.name: Poachers Beware
episodes.overview: A deer poacher is busted, a baby rattlesnake is rescued, a hummingbird evades capture, and a raccoon is released into the wild. The Game Wardens also respond to flooding conditions and a car accident.

episodes.name: Red Flag
episodes.overview: A landowner is spoken to for a second time about illegally hunting dove. An injured deer is found hiding in a shed after being attacked. While pulling over a suspicious vehicle, the Game Wardens notice the driver hiding something under his seat.

episodes.name: Saving the Herd
episodes.overview: Game Warden Eddins assists the local police with an animal cruelty case. Game Warden Richards responds to a trespassing dispute, and Game Warden Roraback relocates a snapping turtle. On the coast, Game Warden Bailey cracks down on fishermen.

episodes.name: Stray Bullets
episodes.overview: Teal season has just begun in El Paso County; an injured hog needs help; Galveston County fishermen are not playing by the rules; a suspicious driver is searched in Chambers County; turtle hatchlings are released on South Padre Island.

episodes.name: Back in the Wild
episodes.overview: Anglers are out all over Texas; in Houston County, a game warden returns after a life-threatening injury; along the coast, fishermen get caught with too many sharks; a protected turtle gets relocated, and anglers on the Gulf learn how to tag fish.

episodes.name: Bucks and Bows
episodes.overview: A hunter is confronted for killing a deer with a gun during bowhunting season; a man is questioned for possessing venomous copperhead snakes; while checking bowhunters at night, a game warden helps find an injured hunter.

episodes.name: Owl Gone Bad
episodes.overview: It's the opening of deer and oyster season in Texas and Game Wardens find illegal undersized oysters; in East Texas, Game Wardens patrol deer camps; an owl is rescued from a chicken coop and set free.

episodes.name: Wildcat Garage
episodes.overview: Deer season is well underway across Texas; in East Texas, Game Wardens find a bobcat a new home and investigate an illegally killed deer; on the coast, the Texas Game Wardens deal with an outstanding warrant.

episodes.name: Panhandle Poachers
episodes.overview: Warden Marshall leads the charge on a poaching investigation; Warden Richards visits an allegedly illegal snake breeder; Wardens Gould and Hickerson try to save an injured pelican; Warden Miller brings a caracara bird to rehab.

episodes.name: Crossing the Line
episodes.overview: With oyster season in full swing, Texas Game Wardens ensure everyone is following the rules on land and water; hunters are investigated for trespassing on private property; game wardens find an oyster boat deckhand with several warrants.

episodes.name: Hunting Hunters
episodes.overview: Across Texas, Game Wardens enforce the law during prime deer season; bad weather conditions lead to a serious car wreck; a tipster reports an injured owl; an harassment issue between neighbors is addressed; illegal deer disposals are investigated.

episodes.name: Finding a Felon
episodes.overview: Game Warden Herchman saves an owl; Game Wardens Richards and McGee team up to work a case in an archery-only county; Game Wardens Benge and King investigate a poaching case.

episodes.name: Pelicans and Poachers
episodes.overview: On the Gulf, oyster boats and fish retailers are inspected; outside San Antonio, a poacher is caught after posting pictures; in East Texas, game wardens patrol deer camps and help a pelican in distress.

episodes.name: Small Town Troubles
episodes.overview: Game wardens are ready for springtime in Texas. Wardens investigate a video of an illegal hunter. A concerned citizen reports a hunter on his property.A fisherman is illegally catching oysters. A game warden smells something fishy going on.

episodes.name: In Hot Water
episodes.overview: Dockery responds to a call about an alligator found near a residential area. Game Wardens find blood in a hunter’s car after he claimed he didn’t shoot anything. Boone follows up on a call about five raccoons making their way into someone’s home.

episodes.name: Trashed
episodes.overview: Across Texas, game wardens work day and night to enforce the law. In East Texas a young woman is served an arrest warrant. A fisherman has no fishing license but plenty of outstanding warrants. Outside Austin, someone illegally dumps a pile of trash.

episodes.name: Deadly Conduct
episodes.overview: Inman and Eddins assist on a manhunt when a suspect runs a constable off the road. An ordinary fishing check in Navarro County leads Amundson to illegal activity. In Jasper County, game wardens patrol an area after receiving trespassing complaints.

episodes.name: Calm After The Storm
episodes.overview: Game Warden Eddins helps a neighbor in need. Reneau responds to a call about a baby red-tailed hawk. Game Warden Richards attempts to serve an arrest warrant. Game Warden Startz patrols solo on the Guadalupe River. And wardens monitor the Rio Grande.

episodes.name: Midnight Manhunt
episodes.overview: A badly injured tortoise needs an innovative procedure. An eagle’s death is investigated. Out on the lake, wardens educate the public on staying safe. As night falls, a car crash turns into a manhunt.

episodes.name: Shrimp And Run
episodes.overview: For Texas game wardens, the unexpected is all part of the routine. A shrimp boat tries to make a run for it. One warden makes some furry friends. A simple trespass warning turns into a trip to jail. A warden helps a woman spiraling out of control.

episodes.name: Rattled
episodes.overview: Game Warden Boone responds to a venomous rattlesnake; game wardens investigate the illegal killing of a goose in the Texas Panhandle; Game Wardens follow up on a tip about a man going over the fishing limit.

episodes.name: Bullets and Lies
episodes.overview: A couple is suspected of killing a deer during off-season; Warden Iles transports orphaned baby armadillos for rehabilitation; Warden Gould searches for a mountain lion that’s lurking near a recreational park in Laredo.

episodes.name: Drug Run River
episodes.overview: Game Wardens Gould and Hickerson chase drug smugglers that crossed the Rio Grande River. Game Warden Boone checks out an injured bird. Game Warden Damron relocates a feisty marsupial and her babies. Amundson and Poole meet a fan.

episodes.name: Old Warrants Die Hard
episodes.overview: A game warden has a run-in with an acrobatic squirrel. A Mexican shrimp boat may have an illegal catch. Fishing without a license leads to jail. A mystery UTV caught-on-tape has a surprising driver. Some kids are found in a dangerous situation.

episodes.name: Lying Dogs
episodes.overview: The Game Wardens patrol the beach, lake, and land, as summer is in full swing. Wardens educate a dog owner about leaving pets in the sun. An under-age drinker tells too many lies. Wardens inspect novice jet skiers on a busy recreational lake.

episodes.name: In the Crosshairs
episodes.overview: Game wardens enforce the law across Texas. A hunting club has a trespassing issue. People are caught attempting to illegally cross the Rio Grande. An argument between neighbors is mediated. Fishermen receive citations on the Gulf of Mexico.

episodes.name: Bucks Collide
episodes.overview: An epic backyard battle between two angry bucks results in a call to game wardens. Kiel springs into action when he responds to a call about a drowning in progress and a simple act of trespassing reveals a serious drug offense.

episodes.name: Sparks Flying
episodes.overview: During the holiday weekend a jet skier is reported missing, while another is caught without a life vest. Warden Kiel witnesses a fist fight during the fireworks, and Warden Cummings handles underage drinkers.

episodes.name: Liars and Trespassers
episodes.overview: Game Warden McGee rushes to a domestic altercation; Zuniga and Roel run into trespassers; Provasnik inspects a potentially stolen jet ski; Richards and McGee team up on an investigation, and a baby squirrel is rescued.

episodes.name: Wild Call
episodes.overview: When a 12-foot gator manages to trap itself in wires, the wardens are determined to set it free. Warden Boone responds to a domestic dispute call, and a grey fox is found trapped in a residential area. Meanwhile, a darted goose chase ensues.

episodes.name: Stag Poaching
episodes.overview: Texas Game Warden Gould responds to the call about an exotic red stag that was shot; in Hunt County, many warrants are dispersed for unpaid fishing violations; Warden Flores and Warden Williams join forces on the last day on patrol.

episodes.name: Confronting The Captain
episodes.overview: In Texas, multiple boats are caught over-harvesting oysters and the wardens must handle an unruly captain. Then, when a fox is found dead on private property, an investigation begins to find the one responsible.

episodes.name: Family Lies
episodes.overview: It's the start of hunting season, dubbed the "Holy Day for Game Wardens". Wardens Inman and Eddins investigate the illegal shooting of two deer. Then, Wardens Stapleton and McGee swap out bass fish in the Bois d'Arc Lake.

episodes.name: Thrill Of The Hunt
episodes.overview: A tense confrontation ensues when Wardens Scott and Gould respond to a call about an illegal deer hunting case. A pair of raccoons find their way to a gas station and must be trapped, and Warden Boone handles a disgruntled hunter at a deer hunting club.

episodes.name: Reckless Behavior
episodes.overview: During deer hunting season, Wardens Gould and Scott respond to a call about finding carcasses on private property. Then, stray bullets are shot into a horse owner's home, while hunters are questioned about hunting illegally.

episodes.name: Anglers, Alcohol And Owls
episodes.overview: In Texas, a woman is found in distress on the side of the highway. Warden Hensz handles an aggressive family of owls, while Warden Bailey responds to a call about underage drinkers holding a fishing tournament.

episodes.name: Confessions of a Poacher
episodes.overview: Warden Richards confronts a suspected poacher for illegally hunting ducks and geese. Wardens Ben and Chelsea Bailey monitor an injured deer running along a busy highway, and a man is arrested after confessing to poaching a deer.

episodes.name: Caught By Surprise
episodes.overview: Warden Price is on a mission to arrest out-of-state hunters with warrants for trespassing and hunting on private property. A young angler is haunted by his past and is taken to county jail, and Warden Richards questions a pair of dishonest fishermen.

episodes.name: Tempers Are Rising
episodes.overview: Warden Cummings deals with an angry man who blew a stop sign. Warden Boone helps chase a trio of armed robbers on the run, and Warden Inman investigates a group of suspected deer hunters for trespassing.

episodes.name: Chasing a Dead Man
episodes.overview: In Llano County, a jet skier’s life is spared after an explosion on the water. When a man fakes his own death, Warden Herchman and Stapleton join forces to track him down, and a man is found trespassing while fishing.

episodes.name: Suspicious Encounters
episodes.overview: A check for a fishing license takes an unlikely turn and an abandoned car is found on private property. Wardens Sellers and Roraback are in pursuit of illicit hunters, and zebra mussels are suspected of being illegally transported in Llano County.

episodes.name: Passing The Torch
episodes.overview: As Warden Richards reminisces on his career during the last day on the job, he races to rescue a cow being attacked by a pack of hunting dogs. At the academy, new recruits wrangle a gator, while anglers are caught illegally fishing.

episodes.name: Wake of Destruction
episodes.overview: Game wardens intervene when an overloaded boat and jet skiers risk lives.

episodes.name: Marshland Massacre
episodes.overview: A slew of poached bird eggs is found while searching for a missing person.

episodes.name: Garage Gator
episodes.overview: In Liberty County, Warden Jake Noxon investigates a family for illegally keeping a pet deer; an alligator roams a garage; Warden Mike Boone joins forces with local police to track down armed suspects after a robbery.

episodes.name: Deadly Spill
episodes.overview: Game Warden Randolph McGee assesses a major gasoline spill in the local water system then tracks down a trash dumping culprit; young jet skiers are confronted, and game warden Mike Boone helps relocate an alligator.

episodes.name: Sunk In Seconds
episodes.overview: Game Wardens rush to help passengers of a sunken boat on Sam Rayburn Lake.

episodes.name: Lake Showdown
episodes.overview: Wardens Sovall and Reneau handle a drunk patron on Sam Rayburn Lake.

episodes.name: Sparking Disaster
episodes.overview: A group is caught throwing out lit cigarettes during wildfire season.

episodes.name: Bracing for Impact
episodes.overview: A routine inspection turns treacherous on the Gulf of Mexico.

episodes.name: Caught in the Crossfire
episodes.overview: Suspicions flare when stray bullets strike an elderly couple's home and their neighbors are questioned. Game Wardens Raj Ataya and Clint Caywood rush to help an injured boater, and an overnight kayak patrol reveals campers throwing caution to the wind.

episodes.name: Guns and Meth
episodes.overview: Wardens bust unlicensed hunters who are also carrying illegal drugs.

episodes.name: Wild Riders
episodes.overview: Reckless jet skiers are caught wreaking havoc at a boat ramp.

episodes.name: No License to Kill
episodes.overview: Foolhardy speedsters run afoul of wardens on a nighttime stakeout mission.

episodes.name: Hunter Games
episodes.overview: Wardens question a felon suspected of illegally hunting with a firearm.

episodes.name: Blood Evidence
episodes.overview: Wardens interrogate a group of hunters suspected of trespassing and theft.

episodes.name: Lake Saviors
episodes.overview: Retired Game Warden Benny Richards returns with a friendly challenge for Game Warden Randolph McGee. A gunshot leads to dubious activity on a night stakeout, and wardens spring into action to save a wakeboarder with a life-threatening injury.

episodes.name: Crash and Burn
episodes.overview: A routine patrol turns intense when Game Wardens Kyle Allison and Dustin Delgado discover an angler is wanted for serious crimes, then rush to the scene of a plane crash. Game Warden Mallory Mitchell confronts backyard hunters in a crowded neighborhood.

episodes.name: Rock Bottom
episodes.overview: Game Warden Kegan Gould crosses paths with a rock collector and uncovers a devastating secret. A teen is caught on camera destroying protected bird nests, and an unruly crowd threatens public safety on Lake Sam Rayburn.

episodes.name: Deception on Deck
episodes.overview: When an oyster captain gets confrontational, Warden Trey Kram discovers one of the crew members has a history with the law; Warden Mike Boone encounters suspicious trespassers; Warden James Cummings celebrates his daughter's graduation

episodes.name: Slaughter at Sea
episodes.overview: While investigating a boat wreck, Warden Jennifer Provaznik discovers a grisly secret; game wardens intervene to save baby turtles being sold on a street corner; a fisherman's oversized fillet sparks suspicion

episodes.name: Lakeside Outlaw
episodes.overview: Matt Kiel and Michael Serbanic investigate a bizarre lakeside encampment; a day at the beach turns ugly when illegal gillnets are discovered, and Matt Maloney protects a neighborhood from trespassers in the border town of Del Rio.

episodes.name: Spying on a Killer
episodes.overview: Game Wardens Justin Eddins and Morgan Inman question a suspicious ATV rider and get a stunning confession; a surveillance operation brings a killer to justice; Warden Derrick Lopez intervenes when trespassers build a bike track on private land.

episodes.name: Armed Invader
episodes.overview: When security footage shows a trespasser with a firearm, game wardens track down and confront the suspect. Game Warden Randolph McGee races to save a deer from a painful end, and Game Warden Mike Boone intervenes when a poaching complaint escalates.

episodes.name: Small Town, Big Trouble
episodes.overview: In small town Texas, game wardens are on the front lines of law enforcement. An elderly couple's front door is shattered by a bullet, a poacher faces jail time, and a routine hunting check takes a surprising dark turn.

episodes.name: Against the Odds
episodes.overview: Warden Jennifer Provaznik handles trespassing anglers; warden Angel Miller tickets out-of-state hunters with a slew of violations.

episodes.name: A Wanted Man
episodes.overview: When an angler flees a routine stop, his strange story exposes a troubling secret. Game Wardens Jamal Allen and Josh Sako get hands-on with a gator living too close to people, and Game Warden Mike Boone responds to a call from hunters of exotic deer.

episodes.name: Trapped on the Rio Grande
episodes.overview: A helicopter races up the Rio Grande to rescue boaters stranded in quicksand. Game Warden Randolph McGee catches a thief when a stolen camera gives him away. And a new game warden finds multiple violations and a man with a warrant - all in one stop.

episodes.name: Camouflaged Felon
episodes.overview: An armed felon behaving strangely interrupts practise at a police firing range. Game Warden Todd Long catches a hunter dumping carcasses in a fishing hole, and a truck submerged in a lake puts first responders in danger.

episodes.name: Hunter's Confession
episodes.overview: Game Warden Mallory Mitchell chases down a fisherman on the run. Game Warden Mike Boone investigates a hunter's confession, oystermen face the consequences for their illegal catch, and game wardens wrangle a gator found dangerously close to people.

episodes.name: Blood, Footprints and Lies
episodes.overview: When a suspicious hunter is caught in a lie, game warden Preston Whisenhunt enlists a K-9 tracker to sniff out the evidence; two men who park illegally in a riverbed are hiding something; game wardens investigate a boat that may have been stolen.

episodes.name: Stranded on the Rio Grande
episodes.overview: Game Warden Randolph McGee surprises a thief with real-time footage from a stolen camera. Game Warden Allison Hatten races to the aid of boaters stuck in quicksand, and a pair of suspected road hunters tell an unlikely story.

episodes.name: Felon on the Border
episodes.overview: A report of human smuggling by jet ski leads game wardens on a beachside chase. Game Warden Dustin Delgado discovers a wanted man fishing illegally on a barge, and reckless ATV riders terrorize a neighbourhood.

episodes.name: Felon on the Firing Range
episodes.overview: A felon in full camo interrupts police firearms training with gunfire of his own. Game Wardens Randolph McGee and Chris Freed set up a hog decoy and lie in wait for lawbreaking hunters, and a man is caught polluting a river with animal remains.

episodes.name: Trail of Lies
episodes.overview: With help from a K9 scent tracker, game wardens gather evidence that a lying hunter may have committed a felony; a duck hunter is caught hiding an illegal bird; game wardens Chelsea and Ben Bailey suspect an unidentified boat may be stolen property.

episodes.name: Violent Tendencies
episodes.overview: When a hunter turns himself in for an illegal kill, Game Warden Bo Hancock uncovers an additional crime that could send him to jail. A fishing stop reveals a wanted man with violent tendencies, and evidence in a truck bed signals a possible crime.

episodes.name: Sinking Boats, Stealing Deer
episodes.overview: Game Warden Allison Hatten discovers a boat with children aboard sinking fast in rough waters. A landowner accuses his neighbour of shooting a trophy buck illegally, and game wardens track down a pair of lawbreaking anglers.
